# `merge=union` keeps both sides of a conflicting hunk instead of raising a
# conflict. Applied only to the append-only roadmap/strategy docs, where
# concatenation is always the correct resolution.
#
# NOTE: during the 12-branch build-stabilization integration this also
# briefly covered route_names.dart and service_locator.dart. Those entries
# were removed afterwards — `union` on source files can silently hide a
# genuine future conflict, so code files must conflict normally.
docs/** merge=union
